description:
If you\&amp;#039;re downloading this it\&amp;#039;s reasonable to assume you already have a passing knowledge of Richard Williams\&amp;#039; long-in-production classic, The Thief and The Cobbler. The film has received theatrical and retail releases, although those cuts aren\&amp;#039;t terribly close, if even remotely so, to Williams\&amp;#039; intentions as he had been removed from the project by this point. That\&amp;#039;s where our man Tygerbug comes in, taking up the challenge of assembling a cut from multiple sources and presenting a version of the film as close to Williams\&amp;#039; original intentions as possible.

This DVD is the third and most current revision of Tygerbug\&amp;#039;s assembly of this cut of the film. Compared to the previous versions, this features massively improved video in many parts and a new audio mix. Some of the bonus features from previous versions of the DVD are no longer included here due to space restrictions, but there are additional discs available that contain these features. I, or whomever is willing to do so, can post these upon request.

For more information on the film and Tygerbug\&amp;#039;s cuts, please visit these websites. Enjoy!
